  "prompt": "What are the places to eat near thapar university, patiala?",
  "response": "Thapar University in Patiala is surrounded by several dining options ranging from casual eateries to more formal restaurants. Here are some popular places to eat near the university:\n\n### Local and Casual Eats:\n1. **Giani Tea Stall**  \n   - Famous for its parathas, chai, and Punjabi snacks, this iconic stall is a hit among students and locals.\n\n2. **Pandit Ji Ki Hatti**  \n   - A small eatery known for its delicious pani puri, chaat, and other street food.\n\n3. **Burger Singh**  \n   - A popular fast-food joint for burgers, wraps, and fries.\n\n4. **Chawla Chicken**  \n   - A favorite for North Indian non-vegetarian dishes, especially their butter chicken and tandoori items.\n\n5. **Virasat Restaurant**  \n   - A budget-friendly spot for Punjabi cuisine, including thalis and curries.\n\n6. **Al Bake**  \n   - Known for its shawarma, rolls, and other quick bites.\n\n### Restaurants with Dine-in Options:\n7. **The Eighth Floor**  \n   - A rooftop restaurant offering a mix of Indian and Continental dishes with a great view.\n\n8. **McLeod Inn Restaurant**  \n   - A multi-cuisine restaurant serving Indian, Chinese, and Continental dishes.\n\n9. **Gazebo Restaurant**  \n   - A fine-dining option with a focus on North Indian and Mughlai cuisine.\n\n10. **Chandigarh Farms**  \n   - Located a short drive away, it\u2019s a great spot for Punjabi food in a rustic setting.\n\n### Cafes and Dessert Places:\n11. **Cafe Coffee Day (CCD)**  \n   - A popular chain for coffee, sandwiches, and snacks.\n\n12. **Barista**  \n   - Another well-known cafe chain for coffee, tea, and light bites.\n\n13. **Sweet House**  \n   - A bakery and sweet shop offering a variety of desserts and snacks.\n\n### Delivery Options:\n14. **Zomato/Swiggy**  \n   - Many local restaurants and cafes listed on these food delivery platforms cater to the Thapar University area.\n\nThese options provide a mix of flavors and cuisines, ensuring there\u2019s something for everyone near Thapar University.",
